This hospital-based study enrolled 50 patients with suspected DENV infection seen at six hospitals in Nepal: STIDH (n = 27); CMC (n = 14); UCMS (n = 2); and the three hospitals from Butwal (n = 7). The sampling sites encompass the southern lowland Terai region from East to West and the hilly region in the central zone (
 Fig 1). The ratio of males to females was 3.5:1 (males 39/50, 78%) and the ages ranged from 12 to 74 years (31.18 Â± 13.61 years). The majority of patients of both sexes were age 16 to 30 years (n = 25) followed by 31 to 45 years (n = 14; 
 Fig 2).
